but I'm not exactly sure to who.

156
00:07:49,650 --> 00:07:53,849
Now, by the way, the frog comes
in two sizes, "large" and "giant".

157
00:07:53,929 --> 00:07:56,489
Now, obviously,
if you win the lottery,

158
00:07:56,570 --> 00:07:58,049
you are springing for the giant one.

159
00:07:58,130 --> 00:08:02,010
But there are currently
only three of them left in stock.

160
00:08:02,090 --> 00:08:04,450
So, the statues are likely
to get more expensive,

161
00:08:04,530 --> 00:08:06,650
because everyone
suddenly wants one,

162
00:08:06,729 --> 00:08:08,489
as they all have
more money to spend,

163
00:08:08,570 --> 00:08:10,729
but there are only three left.

164
00:08:10,809 --> 00:08:13,970
Basically, high demand,
not enough supply,

165
00:08:14,049 --> 00:08:16,530
and that's how we get frog-flation.

166
00:08:16,609 --> 00:08:19,330
So, too much money chasing
a limited supply of goods

167
00:08:19,409 --> 00:08:20,690
can lead to inflation.

168
00:08:20,770 --> 00:08:23,929
And some on the right have seized
on the "too much money" part

169
